I wanted to tell you about this at the very start, but me and my family decided not to disclose it soon.
Few weeks back mummy and papa were tested positive for covid-19.
Not only mummy papa but my uncle,aunt, my nephew Adi (yes that little kid) & even my cousin brothers from ACV team jashan and tanish tested positive for corona
We got the permission for home quarantine for all of them except my chachu and chachi who were in the hospital. (Now they are back at home)

We isolated Mummy, papa & adi in their rooms and took extreme care of them
The first 2 days hit me and muski hard 
We were anxious and very scared, the thought of it sent shivers down our spine
We were too emotional
Hearing about it since last 4 months in news and seeing it up close and personal are 2 very different aspects of coronavirus.
We are so lucky and blessed that my family did not face severe consequences, CANT EVEN IMAGINE WHAT POOR PEOPLE MUST BE GOING THROUGH.
The person that helped the most was muskan, never in my life did i see this girl act so responsibly!

Mummy papa kept telling me to work since last month,
But in the middle of it i couldn‚Äôt bear it with all the anxiety and emotions
so i decided to just go off internet
Today i am very happy and proud to share a good news with you all : 
Mummy-Papa fought covid-19 like true warriors and have recovered from it. 
Chachu,Chachi,Aditya,Jashan & Tanni are recovering from itüôè
We all decided to disclose this news only when everyone recovered because this year already had a lot of bad news and we did not wanted to contribute more to it.

The last weeks showed us a lot, it was a very moving time and it taught us to value the
most important people of our lives.
I request you all to take extreme precautions and be very cautious in this time.Please apna aur apne family ka dhyaan do
I am hoping we all get a vaccine very soon so that no one else suffers this traumatizing pandemic.
Mummy papa it feels good hugging you after so many days
I LOVE YOU SO MUCH
Thank you for being there everyone 
Take extreme care of your family.
@anilchanchlani @deepachanchlani @missmcblush @jashansirwani @tanish_sirwani

DONT SPREAD FALSE RUMORS.
Its my humble request to you all to please read this post
The ‚ÄúCORONOVIRUS‚Äù is a very deadly virus that has suddenly started spreading in china
It has no treatment and can not be cured if reaches the last stage
Thanks to quarantine department of india, we might be safe from this virus from now on as they are building all barriers to make sure this virus does not enter india
But WE ALL SHOULD BE PREPARED as our country is the second most populated country in the world
Please make sure that yoi
1) Always wash your hands with antiseptics like dettol, coronovirus spreads from body fluids or touching something an infected person has touched and then using the same touch on your face/mouth/nose
2) if you have severe cold, running nose, common cold that is with you for days or any severe respiratory problem
Immediately go to the doctor
3) Stop SPITTING, a lot of viruses spread only because of body fluid and the way people spit here already puts us in danger, please DO NOT SPIT and if someone else does this CONDEMN them and tell them about the dangers

Please make sure that you all share this post so that it reaches everyone and we all are aware about it, prevention and safety is better than running for your life in last moments
Use the hashtag #CLEANYOURSELF so that this message reaches everyone
LETS MAKE SURE WE ALL ARE PREPARED TO FIGHT THIS.

I want to tell you all something amazing about this person called ‚ÄúAKSHAY KUMAR‚Äù.
The first time he entered the room my world stopped right there all my life all my videos
my comedy my writing has been inspired from this one man.
I meet him completely awestruck mesmerisingly looking at him, anxious at the same time he comes up to me and starts a conversation.
In a moment he made me comfortable, eased me up and the best part despite being such a mega star i never felt even once that i am just a small youtuber in front of this bollywood biggie.
He made sure he respected my work, he was in it from the start.
The amount of respect he gave to the craft i was shocked to see because i never saw anyone from bollywood before showing so much interest in this small YT integration
I went with expectations of getting a video with him but i came back with immense inspiration.
He sat with me rehearsed the script from start to finish, also let me tell you no other actor has ever rehearsed with me before our video shoots.
He was polite, humble and FUNNY AF
Dude is straight UP HILARIOUS
His antics his way of talking and his style is magical.
He gave me a complete shot in one take
And i was so happy with it but he tells
Me ‚ÄúASHISH CHAL EK AUR KARTE HAI‚Äù
Concluding this i would just say i have loved him all my life but after meeting him my love and respect for him multiplied 100 times
I touched his feet and told him ‚Äúsir aap mere guru ho‚Äù
and he tells me ‚ÄúArre arre kya tu bhi, next time aur ache se karenge‚Äù
Thank you akshay sir for giving me your precious time
I really love you ALOT.
@akshaykumar
